"credit_id":"5e78b3a3357c00001951dbea","department":"Sound","job":"Music Editor"},{"adult":false,"gender":2,"id":23414,"known_for_department":"Art","name":"Ross Dempster","original_name":"Ross Dempster","popularity":0.9065,"profile_path":null,"credit_id":"5e78afc3c8a2d400132224ef","department":"Art","job":"Production Design"},{"adult":false,"gender":0,"id":1823253,"known_for_department":"Writing","name":"Emily Brochin","original_name":"Emily Brochin","popularity":0.2609,"profile_path":null,"credit_id":"5e78ad5b2f3b170017538d9d","department":"Writing","job":"Writer"},{"adult":false,"gender":1,"id":968859,"known_for_department":"Production","name":"Jacqueline Levine","original_name":"Jacqueline Levine","popularity":0.606,"profile_path":null,"credit_id":"5e78b483a055ef00182fd9f1","department":"Production","job":"Executive Producer"},{"adult":false,"gender":0,"id":2576091,"known_for_department":"Editing","name":"Noah Pontell","original_name":"Noah Pontell","popularity":0.1656,"profile_path":null,"credit_id":"5e78af172f3b170014538aef","department":"Editing","job":"Editor"}],"id":79649}},"person_1452028_translations":{"at":1774731924531,"data":{"id":1452028,"translations":[{"iso_3166_1":"US","iso_639_1":"en","name":"English","english_name":"English","data":{"biography":"Reina Ueda is a Japanese voice actress and singer from Toyama Prefecture. She is affiliated with 81 Produce. Beginning her career as a voice actress in 2012, her first main role was Naru Sekiya, the protagonist of the 2014 anime series Hanayamata.","name":"Reina Ueda","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"CN","iso_639_1":"zh","name":"普通话","english_name":"Mandarin","data":{"biography":"上田丽奈是日本女性配音员、歌手。\n\n2011年在第5回81试音选拔中获准优秀奖，并隶属于81Produce。作为声优组合「アニソニア」（Anisoni∀，成员为上田丽奈、高桥李依、林田智惠里与积田加代子）的一员活动。\n\n2014年，在《花舞少女》中出演关谷鸣，成为首次主演。\n\n2015年，获第九回声优奖新人女优奖，之后日本网民有时会在niconico动画中遇到她演出的角色或是本人于生放送出场时打上「新人王上田」或「新人王」的留言。\n\n2016年9月23日歌手出道，唱片公司为Lantis。","name":"上田丽奈","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"ES","iso_639_1":"es","name":"Español","english_name":"Spanish","data":{"biography":"Reina Ueda (上田 麗奈, Ueda Reina, nacida el 17 de enero de 1994) es una actriz de voz y cantante japonesa de la prefectura de Toyama. Actualmente pertenece a 81 Produce. Comenzó su carrera como actriz de voz en 2012, su primer papel principal fue Naru Sekiya, la protagonista de la serie de anime de 2014 Hanayamata.","name":"Reina Ueda","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"KR","iso_639_1":"ko","name":"한국어/조선말","english_name":"Korean","data":{"biography":"","name":"우에다 레이나","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"BR","iso_639_1":"pt","name":"Português","english_name":"Portuguese","data":{"biography":"","name":"Reina Ueda","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"JP","iso_639_1":"ja","name":"日本語","english_name":"Japanese","data":{"biography":"","name":"上田麗奈","primary":true}},{"iso_3166_1":"TW","iso_639_1":"zh","name":"普通话","english_name":"Mandarin","data":{"biography":"上田麗奈是日本的女性聲優和歌手。出身於富山縣，所屬公司為 81 Produce。","name":"上田麗奈","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"SA","iso_639_1":"ar","name":"العربية","english_name":"Arabic","data":{"biography":"","name":"رينا أويدا","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"GR","iso_639_1":"el","name":"ελληνικά","english_name":"Greek","data":{"biography":"","name":"Ρέινα Ουέντα","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"IL","iso_639_1":"he","name":"עִבְרִית","english_name":"Hebrew","data":{"biography":"","name":"ריינה אואדה","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"RU","iso_639_1":"ru","name":"Pусский","english_name":"Russian","data":{"biography":"","name":"Рэина Уэда","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"TH","iso_639_1":"th","name":"ภาษาไทย","english_name":"Thai","data":{"biography":"","name":"เรนะ อุเอดะ","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"UA","iso_639_1":"uk","name":"Український","english_name":"Ukrainian","data":{"biography":"","name":"Рейна Уеда","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"HK","iso_639_1":"zh","name":"普通话","english_name":"Mandarin","data":{"biography":"上田麗奈是日本的女性聲優和歌手。出身於富山縣，所屬公司為 81 Produce。","name":"上田麗奈","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"DE","iso_639_1":"de","name":"Deutsch","english_name":"German","data":{"biography":"Reina Ueda, geboren am 17. Januar 1994 in Toyama, Japan, ist eine japanische Synchronsprecherin (Seiyū) und Sängerin, die der Agentur 81 Produce angehört. Sie entdeckte früh ihre Leidenschaft fürs Performen durch das Schultheater, gewann 2011 den Second Class Grand Prix bei den 81 Produce Auditions und debütierte 2012 in „Inazuma Eleven Go Chrono Stone“, wobei ihre erste Hauptrolle Naru Sekiya in „Hanayamata“ (2014) folgte, die ihr 2015 den Best New Actress Award bei den Seiyū Awards einbrachte. Zu ihren markanten Rollen zählen Kanao Tsuyuri in „Demon Slayer: Kimetsu no Yaiba“, Akane Shinjō in „SSSS.Gridman“, Mallow in „Pokémon: Sun & Moon“, Ganyu in „Genshin Impact“, Shuka Karino in „Darwin's Game“, Reze in „Chainsaw Man“ sowie Figuren wie Miyako Hoshino in „Wataten!“ und Mira Yurisaki in „Dimension W“. Als Sängerin debütierte sie 2016 mit dem Mini-Album „RefRain“, veröffentlichte Singles wie „Sleepland“ (2018) und „Literature“ (2020) und erhielt 2021 den Best Supporting Actress Award.","name":"Reina Ueda","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"CZ","iso_639_1":"cs","name":"Český","english_name":"Czech","data":{"biography":"","name":"Reina Ueda","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"SK","iso_639_1":"sk","name":"Slovenčina","english_name":"Slovak","data":{"biography":"","name":"Reina Ueda","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"IT","iso_639_1":"it","name":"Italiano","english_name":"Italian","data":{"biography":"","name":"Reina Ueda","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"FR","iso_639_1":"fr","name":"Français","english_name":"French","data":{"biography":"Reina Ueda est une doubleuse et chanteuse japonaise.\n\nEn 2011, elle a remporté le prix d'excellence lors de la 5e audition organisée par 81 Produce, et elle a rejoint cette agence. Elle a également fait partie du groupe de doubleuses **Anisoni∀** (Anisonia), composé de Reina Ueda, Rie Takahashi, Chihiro Hayashida et Kayoko Sekita.\n\nEn 2014, elle a obtenu son premier rôle principal en interprétant Naru Sekiya dans *Hanayamata* (*La Danse des Fleurs*).\n\nEn 2015, elle a remporté le prix de la meilleure nouvelle actrice lors de la 9e édition des *Seiyuu Awards*. Depuis, les internautes japonais écrivent parfois les messages « *Shinjin Ou Ueda* » (« Reine des débutantes ») ou simplement « *Shinjin Ou* » (« Reine des débutants ») lorsqu'ils la voient incarner un personnage ou apparaître dans des émissions en direct sur Nico Nico Douga.\n\nLe 23 septembre 2016, elle a débuté en tant que chanteuse sous le label Lantis.","name":"Reina Ueda","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"SE","iso_639_1":"sv","name":"svenska","english_name":"Swedish","data":{"biography":"","name":"Reina Ueda","primary":false}}]}}}}